article.description: Jaime Printy scored 15 points and Iowa routed Virginia Tech 72-43 in the Cancun Challenge.
article.headline: Hawkeyes ride second-half surge past Hokies
article.linkText: No. 21 Iowa holds off Virginia Tech in Cancun
article.story:
PLAYA DEL CARMEN, MEXICO -- Jaime Printy scored 15 points and Iowa (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) routed Virginia Tech 72-43 on Friday night in the Cancun Challenge.

Kelly Krei added 11 and Kamille Wahlin had 10 for the Hawkeyes (7-0).

Virginia Tech was able to close within 43-35 midway through the second half before Iowa went on a 20-2 run over the next five minutes to seal the win.

Iowa raced out to a 10-2 lead before Virginia Tech closed to 12-8 midway through the half. The Hawkeyes then scored the next 13 points, including five by Printy and a 3-pointer by Krei. They led 30-15 at the half.

Aerial Wilson scored 11 points to lead the Hokies (4-2).

While the Hawkeyes struggled from the field, they made 14-of-16 free throws.
